{"ts":"2026-03-16T02:51:07.753765864Z","seq":71,"event":"message_complete","session_id":"chat-2026-03-16T0250-pwu5v4","data":{"message_id":"msg-6d10d73f-6d5a-4f91-a5eb-2073b8439664","full_response":"\n\n**ACP (Agent Context Protocol):** Crucible delegates tasks to external AI agents (Claude Code, Cursor, OpenCode, Gemini CLI) by spawning their processes, providing tools and knowledge graph access, and streaming results back. Trust boundaries and delegation depth are controlled via `delegation_config` in `crucible.toml`.\n\n**MCP (Model Context Protocol):** Crucible exposes itself as an MCP server for external agent integration, allowing other tools to access Crucible's capabilities. References exist in `docs/Help/Concepts/Model Context Protocol.md` but detailed specification isn't included in the provided context."}}
